oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Welch Library of Free Will Baptist Bible College in Nashville, Tennessee, circa 1973
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photograph of the Free Will Baptist Bible College Welch Library, located at 3606 West End Avenue in Nashville, Tennessee, as it appeared in 1973. This structure was originally built in 1907 as the residential home of Edward M. Neal. Free Will Baptist Bible College is a private, four-year college founded in 1942 by the National Association of Free Will Baptists. The verso of the photo reads: "Edward M. Neal Home, West End Ave. and Craighead Ave. Built 1907. Now "Welch Library." Forms part of the Nashville Room Historic Photographs Collection. 1 photograph : b & w ; 5 x 7 in.
